      • canNavigate

        public boolean canNavigate()
        Description copied from interface: Navigatable
        Indicates whether this instance supports navigation of any kind. Usually this method is called to ensure that navigation is possible. Note that it is not called if navigation to source is supported, i.e. Navigatable.canNavigateToSource() returns true. We assume that this method should return true in such case, so implement this method respectively.
        Specified by:
        canNavigate in interface Navigatable
        Overrides:
        canNavigate in class AbstractPsiBasedNode<PsiFile>
        Returns:
        false if navigation is not possible for any reason.

      • getTypeSortKey

        public java.lang.Comparable<PsiFileNode.ExtensionSortKey> getTypeSortKey()
        Description copied from class: ProjectViewNode
        When nodes are sorted by type all objects with same weigh will be sorted using some common algorithm (e.g alpha comparator). This method allows to perform custom sorting for such objects. And default comparison will be applied only if nodes are equal from custom comparator's point of view. Also comparison will be applied only if both objects have not null comparable keys.
        Overrides:
        getTypeSortKey in class ProjectViewNode<PsiFile>
        Returns:
        Comparable object.
